## /overview

**Trigger:** User types `/overview` OR asks "what does my project look like?", "give me a structure report", "map my codebase"

**What to do:**
1. Read `aac.config.yml`
2. Map the actual folder structure (top 3 levels)
3. Check each defined layer exists and has files
4. Report file counts per layer
5. Note any folders that don't fit the layer model

**Report format:**
```
## Structure Overview — [project name]

### Layers
✔ components/ui/        — 4 files (primitives)
✔ components/layout/    — 6 files (orchestration)
✔ components/content/   — 8 files (domain)
✔ components/transition/— 1 file  (page transitions)
✔ hooks/                — 2 files
✔ types/                — 1 file
✔ lib/                  — 1 file

### File types
.tsx    24
.ts      6
.css     3

### Unclassified (review)
- `components/SomeFile.tsx` — not in a layer folder
```

